<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.4.5" />

<note type="unknown">Enter and return to Sinclair L H</note>
<fw type="curatorial">5</fw>
<fw type="letterhead">John G. Neihardt<lb/>
Bancroft, Nebraska</fw>

<opener>
<dateline><date>Mch. 24, '18</date></dateline>


<salute>Dear Comrade:&#8212;</salute>
</opener>

	<p>Send me your magazine for the enclosed dollar. I wish I were able to buy a thousand subscriptions. Sterling gave me a copy of the first issue, and it's great stuff. Your work on Religion promises to be a masterpiece. I read "Spring Song" to my wife, and she wept &#8212; though she is no sentimentalist. Also, I felt something like smoke in my throat.</p>

	<p>Success to you!</p>
<closer>
	
	<salute>Yours,</salute>

<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>
</closer>

<postscript>
<p>P. S. <date>June 16, '18</date></p>

<p>I have only now found a dollar that I could tear away from the Grocer, Butcher, et al, and here it is.</p>
<closer>
<signed>J. G. N.</signed>
</closer>
<p>Will find the price for the  book soon. I'm with you!</p>
</postscript>

</div1>
